title: Jack Meibusch
text:
John Henry "Jack" Meibusch (11 December 1874 - 17 February 1955) was a <a href="rugby%20union">rugby union</a> player who represented in the <a href="Australia%20national%20rugby%20union%20team">Australia national rugby union team</a>.
Meibusch, a <a href="prop%20%28rugby%20union%29">prop</a>, was born in <a href="Surat%2C%20Queensland">Surat, Queensland</a> and claimed one international rugby cap for Australia, playing against Great Britain, at Sydney, on 30 July 1904. His younger brother <a href="Lou%20Meibusch">Lou Meibusch</a> also made a Wallaby appearance in 1912.
